configuration.name: Email
configuration.description: The Users email address

configuration.name: User Password
configuration.description: The Users password

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Account ID
configuration.description: Your account ID. This can be found under Web Services preferences in Netsuite.

configuration.name: NetSuite Role ID
configuration.description: The Role Id of the User (eg 3,4,etc)

configuration.name: Application ID
configuration.description: The ID of your application. This can be found under Integration settings in Netsuite.

configuration.name: NetSuite User ID
configuration.description: The user ID of the application.

configuration.name: NetSuite Partner ID
configuration.description: The Partner ID of the application

configuration.name: NetSuite Company ID
configuration.description: The Company ID of the application

configuration.name: Connect to Sandbox
configuration.description: Connect to Sandbox Set Yes to Sandbox and NO to Connect to Production

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event Notification Basic Authentication UserName
configuration.description: Event Notification basic authentication username

configuration.name: Event Notification Basic Authentication Password
configuration.description: Event Notification basic authentication password

configuration.name: Event Notifications Enabled
configuration.description: Netsuite ERP Beta Event Notifications Enabled

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Used for how often to poll the application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", “idField”: “user.id”, “datesConfiguration”: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", “createdDateField”: “user.created_at”, “createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }

configuration.name: Event Notification Callback URL
configuration.description: Netsuite ERP Beta Event Notification Callback URL

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload
